this woman I was with, she was just talking to me and she just--

320
00:22:57,676 --> 00:23:01,065
her heart rate quickened and I--I think she's tachycardic.

321
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:14,024
She's--she's dead.

322
00:23:15,153 --> 00:23:16,907
There's nothing you can do for her now.

323
00:23:18,896 --> 00:23:24,163
Look, why don't you... go back to the hotel, or home, try and get some rest.

324
00:23:24,265 --> 00:23:26,723
No. I'm gonna stay.

325
00:23:26,889 --> 00:23:28,765
I need to find my mother.

326
00:23:44,350 --> 00:23:47,340
She's hypothermic. Her BP's dropping to 90 over 60.

327
00:23:47,430 --> 00:23:49,045
It may have nicked an artery.

328
00:23:49,996 --> 00:23:54,961
Give her O2 and 2 large-bore I.V.S., wide open.

329
00:24:00,558 --> 00:24:01,645
Miss me?

330
00:24:06,326 --> 00:24:09,956
I bet you wish I were dead in that crash, huh, baby?

331
00:24:10,995 --> 00:24:13,829
Then I'd finally be out of your head.

332
00:24:15,475 --> 00:24:17,067
Is everything all right, doctor?

333
00:24:19,288 --> 00:24:22,892
Uh, yeah, yeah. I'm fine. I just... a little tired.

334
00:24:23,084 --> 00:24:25,807
Uh, I need a--an angiocath.

335
00:24:27,431 --> 00:24:29,059
Am I gonna die?

336
00:24:31,148 --> 00:24:31,970
No.

337
00:24:32,358 --> 00:24:36,307
But  one of your lungs has collapsed, which means that I have to put a needle into your chest 

338
00:24:36,353 --> 00:24:39,634
so that I can reinflate it before I take out the...

339
00:24:39,968 --> 00:24:42,182
implement. Ok?

340
00:24:42,868 --> 00:24:44,439
- Here you go, doctor.
- Thank you.

341
00:24:46,987 --> 00:24:49,907
Why don't you just let me go, baby?

342
00:24:51,986 --> 00:24:54,596
I need some--some clamps, now.

343
00:24:57,188 --> 00:24:58,423
I'm still here.

344
00:24:59,205 --> 00:25:00,284
Here.

345
00:25:00,679 --> 00:25:01,709
There.

346
00:25:01,932 --> 00:25:03,360
And everywhere.

347
00:25:04,037 --> 00:25:07,264
Aren't you tired of carrying me around with you?

348
00:25:07,725 --> 00:25:09,434
Hon, let me go.

349
00:25:10,130 --> 00:25:11,399
Let me die.

350
00:25:14,313 --> 00:25:16,636
Where are the clamps?! Come on, give me the clamps!

351
00:25:16,725 --> 00:25:18,457
She--she's bleeding into the chest.

352
00:25:18,551 --> 00:25:20,268
Don't be afraid, baby.

353
00:25:20,596 --> 00:25:24,791
Death is just the ultimate orgasm of life.

354
00:25:28,991 --> 00:25:30,624
What is this? Give me something that I can use.

355
00:25:30,658 --> 00:25:33,066
This is all we've got. We're running out of instruments.

356
00:25:33,653 --> 00:25:35,044
Well, get me the oxygen.

357
00:25:35,624 --> 00:25:39,100
That's it, baby. I'm letting go.

358
00:25:42,790 --> 00:25:46,674
Yes, baby! I'm almost there.

359
00:25:47,432 --> 00:25:49,380
No. I can't.

360
00:25:49,510 --> 00:25:50,408
Yeah.

361
00:25:50,578 --> 00:25:51,555
I can't.

362
00:25:52,423 --> 00:25:54,307
Put pressure on this now. Come on, cover it.

363
00:25:55,654 --> 00:26:00,369
When you get her to the E.R., I want you to get a chest tube and some x-rays, all right?

364
00:26:02,626 --> 00:26:04,524
I'm not giving up on you, Kimber.

365
00:26:04,689 --> 00:26:06,103
My name is Karen.

366
00:26:06,479 --> 00:26:08,334
I'm sorry. Karen.

367
00:26:08,629 --> 00:26:10,029
You're gonna be fine.

368
00:26:11,633 --> 00:26:15,078
Hey, how am I supposed to see what's going on with all this stuff here?

369
00:26:15,162 --> 00:26:17,278
Try not to move your arms, Mr. Perri.

370
00:26:17,380 --> 00:26:20,159
Don't move your eyes...

371
00:26:20,244 --> 00:26:22,445
Sean, do it now before he comes down, I beg you.

372
00:26:22,775 --> 00:26:25,121
Once he does, he could go into cardiac arrest from the pain.

373
00:26:25,220 --> 00:26:30,116
Set off alarms for me 'cause I'm in love...

374
00:26:32,755 --> 00:26:35,282
I've never performed this procedure with these.

375
00:26:35,388 --> 00:26:37,192
Sean, just do it.

376
00:26:37,372 --> 00:26:39,834
Keep singing, Mr. Perri. Come on, you have a lovely voice.

377
00:26:39,932 --> 00:26:44,145
Thank you. And now in honor of the bride and groom...

378
00:26:44,247 --> 00:26:47,110
When the moon hits your eye

379
00:26:47,206 --> 00:26:52,109
like a big pizza pie, that's amore...

380
00:26:54,130 --> 00:26:58,384
Bells will ring, ting-a-ling-a-ling--  come on. Ting-a-ling!

381
00:27:08,337 --> 00:27:09,906
- We're losing him, Sean.
- I know. I've almost got it.

382
00:27:10,003 --> 00:27:11,015
Do it.

383
00:27:19,453 --> 00:27:20,854
We're losing him, Sean.

384
00:27:20,950 --> 00:27:23,277
I've almost got it. Almost got it.

385
00:27:23,370 --> 00:27:24,446
Sorry.

386
00:27:25,787 --> 00:27:26,750
I got it.

387
00:27:27,431 --> 00:27:28,430
I got it.

388
00:27:38,839 --> 00:27:40,306
He's gone. Call it.

389
00:27:44,703 --> 00:27:46,804
Time of death 2:45 a.m.

390
00:27:47,268 --> 00:27:48,817
Are you all right, Dr. McNamara?

391
00:27:48,916 --> 00:27:50,514
He was gonna sing at his son's wedding.

392
00:27:50,621 --> 00:27:52,988
Yeah, well, that's a shame, but we can't think about that right now.

393
00:27:53,073 --> 00:27:54,491
You gave it your best shot.

394
00:27:56,631 --> 00:27:58,422
We shouldn't have done this here.

395
00:27:58,510 --> 00:28:00,495
There was no way he was gonna make it. There was no way!

396
00:28:00,524 --> 00:28:03,780
The odds around here suck, doctor, but they're the only ones we got.

397
00:28:04,551 --> 00:28:07,265
I've got a severely burned patient that needs an allograft.

398
00:28:07,307 --> 00:28:08,495
This way.

399
00:28:15,780 --> 00:28:17,031
This is bullshit!

400
00:28:17,125 --> 00:28:20,076
The patient's burnt skin has got to be excised to prevent bacterial infection.

401
00:28:20,177 --> 00:28:23,304
I need to cover the exposed tissue to prevent dehydration, atrophy.

402
00:28:23,393 --> 00:28:26,449
All right, all right. So you're suggesting we get donor skin from a human cadaver?

403
00:28:26,537 --> 00:28:28,373
A temporary measure just until we can get him to a burn unit

404
00:28:28,444 --> 00:28:29,848
where they'll do a permanent graft.

405
00:28:29,933 --> 00:28:32,845
A type O universal donor would lessen the chance of an allogenic reaction.

406
00:28:32,951 --> 00:28:35,515
Unfortunately, even if we started searching the morgue,

407
00:28:35,609 --> 00:28:37,264
identification would be impossible.

408
00:28:37,362 --> 00:28:38,724
I know someone.

409
00:28:38,815 --> 00:28:40,988
Her daughter told me she was a universal donor

410
00:28:41,065 --> 00:28:44,151
when we were filling out the identification forms.

411
00:28:44,263 --> 00:28:45,645
She's over here.

412
00:28:45,968 --> 00:28:47,043
Hold that gurney!

413
00:28:55,064 --> 00:28:57,687
Ok. So you'll excise the donor's dermis

414
00:28:57,773 --> 00:28:59,860
so I can cover the exposed tissue on my patient.

415
00:28:59,893 --> 00:29:00,993
Looks like there's plenty to harvest.

416
00:29:01,185 --> 00:29:02,637
How much are we talking about?

417
00:29:02,721 --> 00:29:04,115
Whatever's still usable.

418
00:29:12,453 --> 00:29:15,747
Do you want me to--to skin her?

419
00:29:15,921 --> 00:29:17,181
This is stuff you did in medical school.

420
00:29:17,266 --> 00:29:18,384
I know.

421
00:29:18,910 --> 00:29:19,972
Sorry.

422
00:29:22,984 --> 00:29:24,103
I need a break.

423
00:29:24,213 --> 00:29:25,463
- What? Are you--
- No.

424
00:29:31,691 --> 00:29:33,168
I can do it.

425
00:29:33,776 --> 00:29:34,936
You're not a doctor.

426
00:29:35,057 --> 00:29:36,702
She's already dead. I can't hurt her.

427
00:29:36,790 --> 00:29:39,583
You said yourself, this is stuff you do in med school.

428
00:29:41,816 --> 00:29:44,286
Besides, she'd want me to.

429
00:29:51,353 --> 00:29:53,359
I'll excise the patient's burnt areas.

430
00:29:53,458 --> 00:29:55,041
You'll harvest the layers of skin from the donor.

431
00:29:55,132 --> 00:29:57,259
You've got to do it quickly and deeply, down to the dermis.

432
00:29:57,348 --> 00:29:59,164
We need to cover 4th-degree burns.

433
00:30:02,784 --> 00:30:05,158
Ok, med school, let's do it.

434
00:31:18,189 --> 00:31:20,875
Patient's been taken to the burn center. I think he's gonna make it.

435
00:31:21,216 --> 00:31:22,639
Good job, med school.

436
00:31:23,644 --> 00:31:25,156
I'm not still.

437
00:31:26,398 --> 00:31:28,611
I, uh, dropped out.

438
00:31:30,538 --> 00:31:32,185
That's a damn shame.

439
00:31:44,265 --> 00:31:45,979
Way to go, Helen.

440
00:31:46,756 --> 00:31:48,825
You just hit a home run.

441
00:32:03,741 --> 00:32:04,596
Julia...

442
00:32:11,844 --> 00:32:13,313
We found Erica.

443
00:32:15,603 --> 00:32:17,291
She didn't make it, sweetheart.

444
00:32:21,437 --> 00:32:22,975
Take me to her.

445
00:32:38,093 --> 00:32:41,710
Listen, Julia, the top half of her body is pretty badly burned.

446
00:32:41,750 --> 00:32:43,771
It's practically unrecognizable.

447
00:32:44,060 --> 00:32:46,359
Then how can you be sure it's her?

448
00:32:46,473 --> 00:32:48,766
There's identifying threads of the feather-lift that we gave her.

449
00:32:48,867 --> 00:32:52,507
She's the right height, right age, hair color and...

450
00:32:56,048 --> 00:32:57,186
And what?

451
00:32:59,222 --> 00:33:03,523
And the birthmark on her inner thigh is the shape of a diamond.

452
00:33:04,348 --> 00:33:05,927
It's still visible.

453
00:33:06,851 --> 00:33:08,971
Look, I know it's not that private, but

454
00:33:09,519 --> 00:33:11,055
it's the best I could do.

455
00:33:12,258 --> 00:33:16,313
I'd like to be alone with her for a few minutes, if you don't mind.

456
00:33:45,665 --> 00:33:48,030
Mother, it's Julia.

457
00:33:49,396 --> 00:33:53,523
What I said at the spa, it was only the anger talking.

458
00:33:53,560 --> 00:33:55,733
You know that, right?

459
00:34:11,245 --> 00:34:12,739
Do you remember--

460
00:34:13,772 --> 00:34:15,543
how old was I...

461
00:34:16,156 --> 00:34:19,685
about 5 or 6?

462
00:34:22,124 --> 00:34:25,239
And you and daddy had had this big fight, and...

463
00:34:26,559 --> 00:34:30,130
you took me by the hand, and you said,

464
00:34:31,918 --> 00:34:34,761
"Let's go, Julia. We're leaving."

465
00:34:35,987 --> 00:34:38,242
And we went outside,

466
00:34:39,555 --> 00:34:45,269
and we just walked for a long time in silence, holding hands.

467
00:34:46,321 --> 00:34:48,347
We went to the park...

468
00:34:53,859 --> 00:34:57,551
You showed me how to put a blade of grass in-between

469
00:34:57,652 --> 00:35:01,484
my thumbs and blow on it to make a noise.

470
00:35:01,639 --> 00:35:06,279
And how I laughed and... you took my face in your hands,

471
00:35:06,373 --> 00:35:10,653
and you said, "I love you, little girl."

472
00:35:11,416 --> 00:35:14,753
And I squeezed you so tight,

473
00:35:15,722 --> 00:35:17,275
and I said,

474
00:35:18,344 --> 00:35:20,792
"I love you, too, mommy."

475
00:35:22,524 --> 00:35:25,282
And we both knew it was true.

476
00:35:26,517 --> 00:35:28,130
Do you remember?

477
00:35:41,250 --> 00:35:45,026
And then one day... it wasn't true anymore.

478
00:35:49,755 --> 00:35:52,456
I forgive you for not loving me.

479
00:35:52,584 --> 00:35:54,151
It's ok.

480
00:35:55,484 --> 00:35:57,703
I didn't love you, either.

481
00:36:00,138 --> 00:36:01,447
I just...

482
00:36:02,531 --> 00:36:04,525
craved...

483
00:36:06,434 --> 00:36:09,153
your approval, like it was...

484
00:36:09,445 --> 00:36:11,768
somehow possible to get it.

485
00:36:16,285 --> 00:36:19,094
I saved a life tonight, mother.

486
00:36:19,409 --> 00:36:21,719
No. 2 lives, actually--

487
00:36:22,644 --> 00:36:25,273
a stranger's and my own.

488
00:36:30,590 --> 00:36:32,147
So it's ok.

489
00:36:34,607 --> 00:36:36,656
You can leave now.

490
00:36:39,006 --> 00:36:44,362
I don't need you to tell me who I am anymore.

491
00:38:17,503 --> 00:38:19,270
My mother's dead.

492
00:38:22,420 --> 00:38:24,655
Jules, I'm so sorry.

493
00:38:39,315 --> 00:38:43,305
- I feel so...
- Shaken. I can only imagine.

494
00:38:43,866 --> 00:38:44,842
No.

495
00:38:45,989 --> 00:38:47,031
Free.

496
00:38:51,999 --> 00:38:53,920
Am I a terrible person?

497
00:38:55,360 --> 00:38:57,344
My mother just died and...

498
00:38:59,873 --> 00:39:04,541
and I feel like... everything's gonna be all right.

499
00:39:05,824 --> 00:39:08,683
You're a remarkable person, Jules.

500
00:39:09,747 --> 00:39:12,127
Every time I look at you in there,

501
00:39:12,223 --> 00:39:17,349
so capable and strong, unafraid of any of it.

502
00:39:22,314 --> 00:39:24,976
You would have been a much better doctor than I am.

503
00:39:33,811 --> 00:39:36,884
You know, I always thought I wish the one who could handle anything,

504
00:39:38,232 --> 00:39:40,890
who wasn't afraid to get his hands dirty,

505
00:39:41,809 --> 00:39:44,624
who could deal with all the shit that's just...

506
00:39:46,991 --> 00:39:48,277
part of life.

507
00:39:49,430 --> 00:39:53,403
I never wanted to know about Matt 'cause I couldn't live with the truth.

508
00:39:53,510 --> 00:39:55,650
I never asked about you and Christian

509
00:39:56,112 --> 00:39:59,413
because I couldn't deal with all the questions I'd have to ask about us.

510
00:40:01,500 --> 00:40:04,581
You shouldn't be so hard on yourself.

511
00:40:06,438 --> 00:40:09,880
There's a reason I'm a plastic surgeon.

512
00:40:14,192 --> 00:40:16,962
If something's ugly, I fix it.

513
00:40:18,149 --> 00:40:22,676
What's imperfect, I make perfect. Wipe away the mess. Make it all nice.

514
00:40:23,849 --> 00:40:26,363
I couldn't do what these guys do:

515
00:40:27,138 --> 00:40:30,308
Life and death, losing more than you save,

516
00:40:30,402 --> 00:40:33,704
and moving on to the next, just one after the other.

517
00:40:35,927 --> 00:40:37,191
You could.

518
00:40:37,859 --> 00:40:38,862
Sean--

519
00:40:38,994 --> 00:40:43,830
All these years, all throughout our marriage, I left you to deal with it all:

520
00:40:45,326 --> 00:40:47,675
The mess of raising 2 kids...

521
00:40:51,309 --> 00:40:53,370
an unfaithful husband.

522
00:40:54,639 --> 00:40:56,170
You could hold it all--

523
00:40:56,404 --> 00:40:58,335
the good and the bad and...

524
00:40:59,557 --> 00:41:01,794
all the grays in-between .

525
00:41:08,766 --> 00:41:11,341
I'm not the man I thought I was.

526
00:41:44,702 --> 00:41:45,797
My god.

527
00:41:47,675 --> 00:41:49,785
I've been up all night. I've been trying to reach you.

528
00:41:50,877 --> 00:41:53,575
My cell battery died hours ago.

529
00:41:54,643 --> 00:41:59,126
Well, I called the airport. They weren't releasing any information. Any--any news?

530
00:42:00,765 --> 00:42:01,679
No...

531
00:42:02,665 --> 00:42:03,875
not yet.

532
00:42:04,082 --> 00:42:05,598
Gosh, you must be wiped.

533
00:42:06,587 --> 00:42:09,326
How about I give you a little massage? I have some time until my 7:00.

534
00:42:09,429 --> 00:42:12,674
You can let your feelings out. You can cry. Whatever you need, I'm here for you.

535
00:42:12,764 --> 00:42:14,088
Don't be.

536
00:42:14,390 --> 00:42:15,723
Don't be here.

537
00:42:15,833 --> 00:42:17,380
I want you out.

538
00:42:18,914 --> 00:42:22,666
Look, about yesterday...

539
00:42:23,912 --> 00:42:26,262
sometimes people misinterpret me

540
00:42:26,528 --> 00:42:28,463
until they get to know me.

541
00:42:33,204 --> 00:42:34,698
I know you.

542
00:42:35,043 --> 00:42:39,851
I know you're someone who can only be big by making others feel small.

543
00:42:40,453 --> 00:42:44,043
I know I don't need people like you in my life anymore,

544
00:42:44,159 --> 00:42:46,233
and I know you're fired.

545
00:42:49,418 --> 00:42:51,281
What about my 7:00 rhinoplasty?

546
00:42:51,383 --> 00:42:54,920
Canceled, as are the rest of your surgeries.

547
00:42:56,260 --> 00:42:57,556
You're a bitch.

548
00:42:59,944 --> 00:43:01,126
Maybe...

549
00:43:01,272 --> 00:43:03,342
but at least I'm not yours.

550
00:43:28,725 --> 00:43:33,401
Ahh, sweetheart. I've been waiting for you all night.

551
00:43:33,562 --> 00:43:36,901
I couldn't leave the way things are between us.

552
00:43:39,167 --> 00:43:41,356
Did you hear the news?

553
00:43:41,569 --> 00:43:45,251
That earlier flight you wanted me on crashed.

554
00:43:49,617 --> 00:43:52,101
